Defendant Triston M Sobrilski in court with attorney Mark Emil Kershek.  Kevin Michael Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties have reviewed the PSI and have no corrections.  State makes sentencing arguments.  Defense makes sentencing arguments.  Defendant's mother, Deanna A., makes statement.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

COUNT 1:  

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT 
  - 3 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  - 3 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  5 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*Not to possess any knives/weapons/firearms

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

CONDITION TIME: 9 months.  First 6 months Huber with release for work and/or treatment.  (CREDIT - 2 days). Last 3 months, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  
Defendant to report to Huber by 6:00 p.m. on March 13, 2017.  

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
